    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_436772">I got the feeling it had been designed with the MMO crowd in mind after reading this article <a href="http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=dnd/dramp/20080222a" target="_blank">http://www.wizards.com/default.asp?x...ramp/20080222a</a> <br />
Not sure why, but just something in the way I read it made me feel uneasy with the direction they were taking.  <br />
 <br />
I will admit that I intend on buying the core books when they become available, but that is only to keep the collection up to date.  As they will probably be demoing 4e rules on World Wide Games Day, I will reserve my final judgement until then.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
